NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The bidding over an overcall is different than bidding after an opening bid. Because the overcaller's lower level is lower and the higher level is also lower. The upper limit is about 16 and the lower level is 8 to 9 points. With a strong hand the overcaller should double and correct. So an overcall range is 8-16 points-give or take one.|
PG| ***** 74 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The other points is whether new suits after overcalls are forcing or not. Some experts play they are forcing and some don't and they play the only forcing bid is a cuebid. I like to play they are forcing and use cuebid as a limit raise or better of the bid suit. But you need to decide.|
PG| ***** 75 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Further, because new suits after overcalls are forcing you need more than 9 points. Some make the bid with 4-card suit and some with 5-card suit. Here North has all the requirements to bid 1S over my 1D overcall. However, if you remove the @CK-though the 3 points is dubious-North should pass the 1D overcall.|
