NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That is not completely correct. After 1C opening with 6-9/bad 10 you can and you should bid your 4-card major. However, Walsh does not say that you should not bid 1D with no 4-card major. Here North does not have 4-card hearts or 4-card spades and can bid 1D. There, even if you play Walsh 1D is a better bid than 1N.|
