Walsh is a treatment in response to partner's 1C opening in a standard American or 2/1 type system. The treatment works equally well if you play better minor or short club. When partner opens 1C the standard responses are up-the-line and one bids a 4-card diamonds suit in preference to a 4-card hearts or spades suit. Playing Walsh you ignore a 4 or 5-card diamonds suit and respond in the 4-card major with a weak hand. Consider the following examples.|
